{
  "text": "The quantified self is difficult to precisely specify and review because it often refers to the general trends for data to be accessed by populations of consumers, rather than employees or other groups per se. Organizations now face a general blurring of a portfolio of relationships beyond just customers-employees, families, communities, teams and other partners are all likely to orbit data flows and transactions [CITATION_1] .",
